{"id":27389,"title":"Make serotonin and naloxone drug plates","title_html":"<p>Make serotonin and naloxone drug plates<\/p>","image":{"source":"https:\/\/www.protocols.io\/img\/default_protocol.png","placeholder":"https:\/\/www.protocols.io\/img\/default_protocol.png"},"doi":"dx.doi.org\/10.17504\/protocols.io.6y5hfy6","doi_status":2,"uri":"make-serotonin-and-naloxone-drug-plates-6y5hfy6","type_id":1,"published_on":1567192210,"parent_protocols":[],"parent_collections":[],"version_id":0,"created_on":1567188723,"categories":null,"creator":{"name":"Serena Ding","affiliation":null,"affiliations":[{"affiliation":null,"url":null,"is_default":1}],"username":"serena-ding","link":null,"image":{"source":"\/img\/avatars\/011.png","placeholder":"\/img\/avatars\/011.png"},"badges":[{"id":4,"image":{"source":"\/img\/badges\/gold.svg","placeholder":"\/img\/badges\/gold.svg"},"name":"Gold power author!"}],"research_interests":null,"blocked_by_you":false,"blocked_you":false},"journal":null,"journal_name":null,"journal_link":null,"article_citation":null,"public":1,"has_versions":0,"link":null,"total_collections":0,"number_of_steps":11,"authors":[{"name":"Serena Ding","affiliation":"Imperial College London","affiliations":[],"username":"serena-ding","link":null,"image":{"source":"\/img\/avatars\/011.png","placeholder":"\/img\/avatars\/011.png"},"badges":[],"research_interests":null,"blocked_by_you":false,"blocked_you":false}],"versions":[],"groups":[],"has_subprotocols":0,"is_subprotocol":1,"is_bookmarked":0,"can_be_copied":1,"can_remove_fork":1,"forks_count":{"private":0,"public":0},"access":{"can_view":1,"can_remove":0,"can_add":0,"can_edit":0,"can_publish":0,"can_get_doi":0,"can_share":1,"can_move":1,"can_move_outside":1,"can_transfer":1,"can_download":1,"is_locked":0},"steps":[{"id":807727,"guid":"822C0E74986E49738E8B451488224D25","previous_id":null,"previous_guid":null,"modified_on":0,"protocol_id":0,"components":[{"id":1054723,"guid":"9A35F5CDB1454519A5E32DABD821F3CA","order_id":1,"type_id":6,"title":"Section","source":{"title":""}},{"id":1054724,"guid":"C38171C72A3D47CDBCEC0591685DF597","order_id":1,"type_id":1,"title":"description","source":{"description":"<div class = \"text-blocks\"><div class = \"text-block\">First identify the drugs (serotonin and naloxone) to be used in the study and ensure that they are correctly labelled and handled.<\/div><\/div>"}}],"cases":[],"data":null,"section":null,"section_color":"","critical":null,"critical_id":null,"duration":0},{"id":807728,"guid":"570E5130A85041D198BFBBB6138D05E4","previous_id":807801,"previous_guid":"9085FE70CB5511E99DC5C7B92CB7F6A2","modified_on":0,"protocol_id":0,"components":[{"id":1054723,"guid":"E614123C002E4BF0BC2BA50751A3BC52","order_id":1,"type_id":6,"title":"Section","source":{"title":""}},{"id":1054724,"guid":"7F9A1C3A6D5E4A469376D013AE68D89C","order_id":1,"type_id":1,"title":"description","source":{"description":"<div class = \"text-blocks\"><div class = \"text-block\">Since these are powered compounds, calculate the desired weight required for 10 mL of serotonin agar (at 20 mM final concentration), and for 1 mL of 10X naloxone stock solution (10X is 100 mM, for 10 mM final concentration). These volumes will give 3 drug plates each.<\/div><\/div>"}}],"cases":[],"data":null,"section":null,"section_color":"","critical":null,"critical_id":null,"duration":0},{"id":807729,"guid":"53C60FFE8BB34939BB103EE4A6A90D52","previous_id":807752,"previous_guid":"7CF8AEA0CB5211E99DC5C7B92CB7F6A2","modified_on":0,"protocol_id":0,"components":[{"id":1054723,"guid":"76563CAAFF8143FCB2BD3D2285DB6D4F","order_id":1,"type_id":6,"title":"Section","source":{"title":""}},{"id":1054724,"guid":"A838A8A3244649C395AF750D92DA8AC1","order_id":1,"type_id":1,"title":"description","source":{"description":"<div class = \"text-blocks\"><div class = \"text-block\">Inside a fume hood, with an analytical balance weigh out the desired amount of serotonin and leave aside. Weigh out the desired amount of naloxone and transfer the powder into a 1.5 mL Eppendorf tube labelled with the compound and the final concentration. To the naloxone tube, add 1 mL sterile water to make up the 10X stock solution, and close the lid of the Eppendorf tube. <\/div><\/div>"}}],"cases":[],"data":null,"section":null,"section_color":"","critical":null,"critical_id":null,"duration":0},{"id":807731,"guid":"CC9A202939CF4AB3AE53DBFDAC598897","previous_id":807782,"previous_guid":"F81AC9A0CB5311E99DC5C7B92CB7F6A2","modified_on":0,"protocol_id":0,"components":[{"id":1054723,"guid":"9DDFB23EA6E1422DA4F7841607F8A45D","order_id":1,"type_id":6,"title":"Section","source":{"title":""}},{"id":1054724,"guid":"42057EFCAFDC4D00B33CCBD7BF863317","order_id":1,"type_id":1,"title":"description","source":{"description":"<div class = \"text-blocks\"><div class = \"text-block\">Take the naloxone stock solution tube out of the fume hood. To ensure the compound is dissolved fully, vortex the Eppendorf tubes (ensuring the lid is firmly in place) at setting 10 for 30 seconds. <\/div><\/div>"}}],"cases":[],"data":null,"section":null,"section_color":"","critical":null,"critical_id":null,"duration":0},{"id":807752,"guid":"7CF8AEA0CB5211E99DC5C7B92CB7F6A2","previous_id":807728,"previous_guid":"570E5130A85041D198BFBBB6138D05E4","modified_on":0,"protocol_id":0,"components":[{"id":1054723,"guid":"39D5D21586344E8496CE930E860E7B03","order_id":1,"type_id":6,"title":"Section","source":{"title":""}},{"id":1054724,"guid":"1C2655671F1A468DB26FFC09DF1C8A10","order_id":1,"type_id":1,"title":"description","source":{"description":"<div class = \"text-blocks\"><div class = \"text-block\">Make up 500 mL low peptone NGM agar and put it on autoclave.<\/div><\/div>"}},{"id":1054725,"guid":"233B2FADBDA045C986AB861736E28E78","order_id":2,"type_id":26,"title":"notes","source":{"id":0,"parent_id":0,"uri":"","title":"","body":"<div class = \"text-blocks\"><div class = \"text-block\">Do not attempt to use a smaller volume even though not much agar is required for drug plate preparation, as chemical weights will be too small to be measured accurately. <\/div><\/div>","created_on":0,"changed_on":0,"creator":{"name":" ","affiliation":"","affiliations":[],"username":"","link":null,"image":{"source":"","placeholder":""},"badges":[],"research_interests":null,"blocked_by_you":false,"blocked_you":false},"comments":[]}}],"cases":[],"data":null,"section":null,"section_color":"","critical":null,"critical_id":null,"duration":0},{"id":807753,"guid":"992EF8E0CB5211E99DC5C7B92CB7F6A2","previous_id":807729,"previous_guid":"53C60FFE8BB34939BB103EE4A6A90D52","modified_on":0,"protocol_id":0,"components":[{"id":1054723,"guid":"B95024AA62794EFCA5900A4A4F1C705F","order_id":1,"type_id":6,"title":"Section","source":{"title":""}},{"id":1054724,"guid":"50DE4F450CBB4B04937EB7A0EA5003F2","order_id":1,"type_id":1,"title":"description","source":{"description":"<div class = \"text-blocks\"><div class = \"text-block\">When the autoclave cycle is done, add salts as normally required.<\/div><\/div>"}}],"cases":[],"data":null,"section":null,"section_color":"","critical":null,"critical_id":null,"duration":0},{"id":807782,"guid":"F81AC9A0CB5311E99DC5C7B92CB7F6A2","previous_id":807753,"previous_guid":"992EF8E0CB5211E99DC5C7B92CB7F6A2","modified_on":0,"protocol_id":0,"components":[{"id":1054723,"guid":"7D6B428C71AE410FA4EC46055BC27C1F","order_id":1,"type_id":6,"title":"Section","source":{"title":""}},{"id":1054724,"guid":"03935ABE89A54132B01D13770B3D3492","order_id":1,"type_id":1,"title":"description","source":{"description":"<div class = \"text-blocks\"><div class = \"text-block\">Remove 10 mL of molten low peptone NGM agar, take it to the fume hood and add the pre-weighed serotonin to achieve 20 mM final concentration. Mix well. Dispense 3 mL into each of three pre-labelled plates using a 10 mL serological pipette. Let serotonin plates set.<\/div><\/div>"}}],"cases":[],"data":null,"section":null,"section_color":"","critical":null,"critical_id":null,"duration":0},{"id":807785,"guid":"63AE9CF0CB5411E99DC5C7B92CB7F6A2","previous_id":807731,"previous_guid":"CC9A202939CF4AB3AE53DBFDAC598897","modified_on":0,"protocol_id":0,"components":[{"id":1054723,"guid":"757DD9DA189D40FB83C5844B05719D1A","order_id":1,"type_id":6,"title":"Section","source":{"title":""}},{"id":1054724,"guid":"7EBEDEB3277A48BDB60E12C3B065C80C","order_id":1,"type_id":1,"title":"description","source":{"description":"<div class = \"text-blocks\"><div class = \"text-block\">Using a different 10 mL serological pipette, draw up 10 mL of molten agar (without serotonin) and dispense 3 mL each into a different set of three pre-labelled plates. Let the plates set (these will become the naloxone plates). <\/div><\/div>"}}],"cases":[],"data":null,"section":null,"section_color":"","critical":null,"critical_id":null,"duration":0},{"id":807787,"guid":"98735F20CB5411E99DC5C7B92CB7F6A2","previous_id":807798,"previous_guid":"FA95BF40CB5411E99DC5C7B92CB7F6A2","modified_on":0,"protocol_id":0,"components":[{"id":1054723,"guid":"3CE6EB99EAF14119B5125D2F22201C99","order_id":1,"type_id":6,"title":"Section","source":{"title":""}},{"id":1054724,"guid":"9945D636FBBB4940AF9CEC9D925F804C","order_id":1,"type_id":1,"title":"description","source":{"description":"<div class = \"text-blocks\"><div class = \"text-block\">Wrap drug plates in foil and leave them overnight at 4\u00b0C to let the drugs diffuse. Use for experiments immediately the next day. <\/div><\/div>"}}],"cases":[],"data":null,"section":null,"section_color":"","critical":null,"critical_id":null,"duration":0},{"id":807798,"guid":"FA95BF40CB5411E99DC5C7B92CB7F6A2","previous_id":807785,"previous_guid":"63AE9CF0CB5411E99DC5C7B92CB7F6A2","modified_on":0,"protocol_id":0,"components":[{"id":1054723,"guid":"598BBDEEC1EF44A39B0355AD803C81DC","order_id":1,"type_id":6,"title":"Section","source":{"title":""}},{"id":1054724,"guid":"74B6B9F6DAA64468B1785496F8AC7203","order_id":1,"type_id":1,"title":"description","source":{"description":"<div class = \"text-blocks\"><div class = \"text-block\">Add 300 \u03bcL of 10X naloxone stock solution on top of each plate from the last step. Let these plates dry in a laminar flow hood for 3 hours. <\/div><\/div>"}}],"cases":[],"data":null,"section":null,"section_color":"","critical":null,"critical_id":null,"duration":0},{"id":807801,"guid":"9085FE70CB5511E99DC5C7B92CB7F6A2","previous_id":807727,"previous_guid":"822C0E74986E49738E8B451488224D25","modified_on":0,"protocol_id":0,"components":[{"id":1054723,"guid":"23DBE9516A09425AA3F2406344E95FE2","order_id":1,"type_id":6,"title":"Section","source":{"title":""}},{"id":1054724,"guid":"03A2DA835CBE4754BF1D88791B3568BE","order_id":1,"type_id":1,"title":"description","source":{"description":"<div class = \"text-blocks\"><div class = \"text-block\">Get six 35 mm petri dishes and label three as serotonin (20 mM) plates and three as naloxone (10 mM) plates.<\/div><\/div>"}}],"cases":[],"data":null,"section":null,"section_color":"","critical":null,"critical_id":null,"duration":0}],"document":null,"materials":[],"description":"<div class = \"text-blocks\"><div class = \"text-block\">Protocol for making a set of three serotonin drug plates and a set of three naloxone drug plates. Serotonin (20 mM) is added to molten agar, whereas naloxone (10 mM) is made into a 10X stock solution in water first before being spread over agar plates to achieve the final concentration. Each 35 mm drug plate contains 3 mL low peptone NGM agar and the drug, and is always made up fresh the day before imaging experiments. <\/div><div class = \"text-block\"><span>For naloxone methods, refer to <\/span><a href=\"https:\/\/www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov\/pubmed\/25898004\" style = \"text-decoration:underline;color:blue;cursor:pointer;\"><span style = \":;\">https:\/\/www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov\/pubmed\/25898004<\/span><\/a><span>. <\/span><\/div><\/div>","changed_on":1567192210}